A commenter on the right to install bulletproof glass post writes,

I think that with a decently intelligent lawyer that laws that establish a "duty to retreat" would be found unconstitutional. Retreat? A duty of Americans of any stripe? Pretty much a concept that would boggle the mind of the founders....

Well, it turns out that Founding-era views on this subject were rather more complex than our guesses -- based on our sense of their world-view -- might suggest.
